        "created_at": "2018-07-12T03:11:33.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><strong><span class=\"bbcode-u\">2014 Jean-Claude Ramonet Chassagne-Montrachet 1er Cru Les Ruchottes</span></strong><br>\nNose of matchstick, lemons, pears, and herbs to start. The matchstick blew off somewhat to let the tart yellow fruit, herbaceousness, and, of course, the mint show through. On the palate the fruit is somewhat subdued and dominated by very linear acidity. I still loved it for its precision and purity though. It\u2019s always a real treat to drink a wine this singular and racy. Hold until at least 2020.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
